# The backend base URL is AUTO-DETECTED by default:
# the app calls the backend on the same host it was opened from, port 4000.
#   - open http://localhost:5173        -> API http://localhost:4000/api
#   - open http://192.168.68.104:5173   -> API http://192.168.68.104:4000/api
# So accessing the console from another device on the LAN works with no config.
#
# Only set VITE_API_URL to pin a specific/remote backend (e.g. a deployed API).
# A localhost value here is IGNORED when the page is opened from another device.
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.your-company.com/api
